SIMPLE: pick_off
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pick off
<hw>Pick" off</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Baseball)</fld> <def>to put out a baserunner who is off base by
tagging him/her, especially by a quick throw from the pitcher or
catcher.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>to shoot so as to kill or disable, especially one by
one from a position or in a situation where the target is unable to
return fire at the shooter; -- used commonly of sniper fire.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧The sniper <ex>picked off</ex> a dozen passersby from the tower
before he was shot down by police.⟦rdquo⟧⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Football)</fld> <def>to intercept (a
pass).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pickpack</ent>⟦br⟧
